@jayakarteek thanks for the explanation :)
I thought that ACS would configure those parameters automatically. The way you described it feels like ACS is not limiting the use of CPU for VMs created in VMware systems. 

I was checking the code, and there is this piece here: `com.cloud.hypervisor.vmware.util.VmwareHelper.setBasicVmConfig(VirtualMachineConfigSpec, int, int, int, int, int, String, boolean)`. At line 634 ACS is setting the CPU limit if CPU cap is enabled. Isn't that information available to be retrieved later (when we get the stats of a VM)? I know, this will only work with CPU cap. However, we could retrieve that CPU limit configuration, if it is '-1', we could then retrieve the CPU speed of the host (and use it to calculate the percentage of usage), is it possible? Or do you think it brings much trouble for the code?

